## Getting Started

How to get started with Hyperapp Gizmo for busy people. Let's say you have 5 minutes. This section is optional too. If you use this section, include a code example as follows.

Our first example is what the example is about and what you can do with it. Go ahead and [try it online](https://codepen.io/hyperapp/).

```js
import { app } from "hyperapp"
import { withGizmo } from "hyperapp-gizmo"
import { withMischief } from "hyperapp-mischief" 

// ...

withGizmo(withMischief(options)(app))(state, actions, view, document.body)
```

## Installation

Install with npm or Yarn.

<pre>
npm i <a href=https://www.npmjs.com/package/hyperapp-gizmo>hyperapp-gizmo</a>
</pre>

Then with a module bundler like [Rollup](https://rollupjs.org) or [Webpack](https://webpack.js.org), use as you would anything else.

```js
import { gizmo } from "hyperapp-gizmo"
```

If you don't want to set up a build environment, you can download Hyperapp Gizmo from a CDN like [unpkg.com](https://unpkg.com/hyperapp-gizmo) and it will be globally available through the <samp>window.gizmo</samp> object. If your library's name is a compound word, use <samp>window.camelCase</samp>.

```html
<script src="https://unpkg.com/hyperapp-gizmo"></script>
```

